metadata.name: odium #36
metadata.description:
The idea behind "odium" is to mix the two previous works to create a new art, which maintains similarities with the previous projects, but also with its differences and peculiarities.

"odium" is based on an algorithm that I've been exploring since the "radium" and "illusions" projects. So this is the last of the series.

It is composed by with grainy/noise and flowfields, creating a glitch effect as it is finishing to render.
"odium" have random colormaps instead a configured palette system, patterns of growth and plays with randomized blendModes and colorModes, 
and I name it "odium"  because the form it grows and glitch reminds me how the hate sometimes slowly consume the mind.

This is a project made in p5.js


Omar Lobato, 04/29/2022.

metadata.name: Plottable Fibers #1
metadata.description:
More info: https://greweb.me/plots/465

Spring season is here! Plottable Fibers explore the beauty of Perlin noise simulating the behaviour of sprouting in Nature. There are many combination of parameters at stake: different intensity of noises, different width and elevation, different inks,...

The digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art: Owning this NFT confers the right to request a physical plot (A4) – this is an optional decoupling as you can already enjoy the digital version:
- The digital representation simulates fountain pen drawing on paper. art published via a digital NFT on Tezos.
- Utility token to the physical world: Right Click Save to get the SVG recipe. using @greweb's services at https://greweb.me/plots/nft but also for any artist to interprete it with their own materials.

@greweb – 2022 – tech: WebGL + Rust + WASM – CC BY-SA 4.0 https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

metadata.name: abstraction #74
metadata.description:
Diagrams of patterns on spheres, planets, fields, and platonic solids rendered isometrically. Ink on paper (on js).

Press DOWN to save an SVG suitable for plotting (or laser etching).
Press UP to save a 2400 x 2400 png. If you need a bigger image, zoom out and refresh, the canvas will fit the window.

Physics is fundamentally idealist. We search for simple rules from which the complexities of the universe emerge. But real systems are exceptionally complex, closed-form solutions are the exception. The deeper we dive into the fundamental nature of the universe, the less clear the rules become. Are the rules we've developed fundamental, or are they empirical approximations?

metadata.name: Omega Point #113
metadata.description:
In the collapsing universe approaching singularity, the last remaining cybernetic organisms encounter the state of infinite knowledge, information, and computational resources.
Although the living creatures in the Omega Point are destined for imminent destruction, they experience infinite life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'space' - improve image quality
'f' - increase rendering speed

The image quality gradually improves over time, up to a certain level. To reach the maximum quality, press 'space'.
The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.
Requires WebGL2.

metadata.name: Bad Habits #60
metadata.description:
Get into Bad Habits...
  
Bad Habits is a collaboration project between me and evilnft.

This is a lottery style png layers project with generated background and layout.

 - 10 text banners
- 8 layouts
- 2 layout styles : sketchy, blocks
